<section containing-doc="D.C. Code" xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:codified="http://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="http://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify">
  <num>44-105.07</num>
  <heading>Full disclosure.</heading>
  <text>A resident shall have the right to full disclosure of contract terms and billing practices that are fair and reasonable.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 13-127" type="History">June 24, 2000, D.C. Law 13-127, § 507, 47 DCR 2647</annotation>
